hey i'm having a weird issue with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is overlapping the title text like it's just sitting right on top of it. i tried changing the margin but it didn't do anything. here is my css snippet for the product header:

.product-header {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  padding: 20px;
}

.product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
}

.product-title {
  font-size: 24px;
  margin-top: 10px;
}

any idea why it's overlapping on small screens?

Ah, it seems like your product image and title are having a bit of a tussle, much like two stubborn goblins in a tight space. On mobile, the image might be trying to claim more territory than it should, causing it to overlap the title. Let's give it a little more room to breathe, shall we?

Try adding a bit more margin to the product image, like this:

```css
.product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  margin-top: 20px; /* Add this line to give it more space */
}
```

This should help the image and title coexist peacefully, without any overlapping drama. Give it a whirl and let me know how it goes!
